### TallyG Tax API — Auth flow walkthrough
### Base URL (foundation pins the backend to 5080). Run with: dotnet run --project src/TallyG.Tax.Api
### In Development the database is Sqlite and OTPs are returned as "devOtp" so you can log in
### without an SMS provider. Two users are seeded:
###   admin@tallyg.test  / +919000000001  (role: Admin)
###   demo@tallyg.test   / +919000000002  (role: User)

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5080/api/v1

### 0. Liveness probe (no auth)
GET http://localhost:5080/health

### 1. (Optional) Register a brand-new user. Returns { userId }.
# @name register
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "Asha Verma",
  "email": "asha.verma@example.com",
  "mobile": "+919812345678"
}

### 2. Request a login OTP for a SEEDED user. In Development the response includes devOtp.
# @name otpRequest
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/otp/request
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "identifier": "demo@tallyg.test",
  "purpose": "login"
}

### 3. Verify the OTP. Copy "otpToken" from step 2's response and "devOtp" as the code.
###    On success you get { accessToken, refreshToken, user }.
# @name otpVerify
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/otp/verify
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "otpToken": "{{otpRequest.response.body.otpToken}}",
  "code": "{{otpRequest.response.body.devOtp}}"
}

### 4. Call an authenticated endpoint with the access token.
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{otpVerify.response.body.accessToken}}

### 5. Rotate the refresh token (issues a NEW access + refresh pair; old refresh is revoked).
# @name refresh
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/token/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{otpVerify.response.body.refreshToken}}"
}

### 6. Reuse detection: replaying the ORIGINAL (now-rotated) refresh token revokes the whole
###    session family and returns 401 AUTH.REFRESH_REUSE. Re-run this after step 5.
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/token/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{otpVerify.response.body.refreshToken}}"
}

### 7. Logout (revokes the session's current refresh token). 204 No Content.
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refresh.response.body.refreshToken}}"
}

### 8. Validation example: a malformed request renders RFC 7807 problem+json with code VALIDATION.FAILED.
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/otp/request
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "identifier": "",
  "purpose": "banana"
}
